title: Part 5
content:
Part 5

IT WAS FINALLY getting down to the three-hour party's last thirty minutes.

I managed to secure enough funding to continue operations, including a reunion with Sakayanagi.

I also found out that there were people waiting for my return to politics.

"Ayanokouji-sensei! May I have a moment of your time?"

"And you are—"

"It’s a great honor to meet you! I’m Kanzaki. Kanzaki Tomohiro from Kanzaki Engineering."

"President Kanzaki, it’s an honor to meet you too."

I remembered when the White Room was first launched, some conglomerates were informed about it, and Kanzaki Engineering was one of the companies that had eagerly offered to invest.

However, as the company was relatively new and had few political connections, I ultimately declined due to our circumstances, but he didn’t show any displeasure and even managed to provide a small amount of investment capital two years later.

"This is my son, Ryuuji. Say hello."

"…I’m Kanzaki Ryuuji."

The child quietly greeted me, looking away.

I see. That was the child from earlier.

"He seems like a bright young man."

"He’s my pride and joy. I want him to excel in both academics and martial arts, and besides karate and judo, we’ve also provided him with all possible education through cram schools and private teachers."

"I could tell that you'd be passionate about education, President Kanzaki."

"In karate, he was even praised by the assistant instructor recently. He said that he has the skills of a black belt at this point already."

"Ah, he seems to be growing up well."

However, if that story was true, there was something that didn’t quite add up.

I politely excused myself from the company president and decided to address Ryuuji.

"I want to ask you something. Earlier, you saw another child being bullied nearby, yet you didn't attempt to help in any concrete way."

"…That’s…"

"Of course, there were more of them than you. However, I heard from President Kanzaki that you're capable yourself. Couldn’t you have thought of a way?"

Pretending to be ignorant of the circumstances, I posed such a question.

"It’s none of my business."

He said, awkwardly averting his gaze.

"Indeed, you weren’t the cause of the conflict. However, if you had helped, you could've gotten him to owe you. That debt could prove beneficial to you in the future."

"…"

"If you don’t have the power to help, you might as well just give up and run away. But if you do have the power and don't use it, then you're a fool."

I had no real interest in the child, but I spoke passionately and placed my hand on the boy’s head.

"Think carefully, worry well, and grow up to be a fine adult. Become an adult who can help others. Support your father, and eventually, take the lead and drive the company forward."

By giving him a lecture in front of President Kanzaki, it'd be difficult for him to treat us poorly or withdraw his investment. After all, it’s always better to keep pulling in as much money as possible.

"…Um, thank you… I’ll think about what I can do."

Moved by my words, his expression softened, and he bowed his head happily.
